Thaxtan, you are off on much of that.

For the best definition of what each stat IS, make a character.  Point to each stat and a box will tell you about it.

But, for a quickie explanation:

STR - effects encumberance, attack rating (partially), and damage.  Is also used in Blacksmithing if higher than your WIS/INT.

STA - effects HP and I believe it also adds to the new Endurance bar.  This bar being new makes it so I'm not 100% on that.

AGI - basically just effects AC.  However, it also partially effects how much damage you take.

DEX - increases the chances of procs and in some tradesills can be used as the primary over WIS/INT if it's higher than either.

WIS - priest mana (clr/dru/shm/pal/bst)

INT - caster mana (wiz/mag/enc/nec/shd/bard)

CHA - effects pricing, charms, lulls

Usually one point change won't do much.  However, there are levels that once hit make a big difference.  For example, 75 AGI is MUCH better than 74.  However, 98 isn't too much better than 75.  Whether this goes for other stats besides AGI, I'm not certain.  I know there's a line around 112 for CHA.

I think that answers your question.  I would advise going to the class forum that you are interested in.  They can give you advice as to what stats are more important and a general idea of how many points to put in what stat.

